More than 700 South Africans have fallen ill and more than 60 have died in the current outbreak of listeriosis. The source of the contamination is not yet known and government has declared it a notifiable disease. At a media briefing hosted by the National Press Club in Pretoria on Thursday representatives of food producers, manufactures and retailers explained their role in curbing the disease and food safety in general. Watch these videos to learn what they had to say:   